&gt;Q: *&quot;The first key of my host_var has a :. Like so,&quot;*

    openconfig-vlan:vlans:

A: There are **variables** in in host_var no **keys**. Quoting from [Creating valid variable names](https://docs.ansible.com/ansible/latest/user_guide/playbooks_variables.html#creating-valid-variable-names):

&gt; &quot;Variable names should be letters, numbers, and underscores. Variables should always start with a letter.&quot;

There is only one idea available. Fix the syntax.

&lt;hr&gt;
