To flatten the array, you can use the spread operator when updating the state. E.g.

    const allCategories = [...firstCategories, ...secondCategories];

where firstCategories and secondCategories are arrays themselves. This will create a single flattened array.

To remove duplicates, you either need to iterate through each category as you&#39;re adding them and check if it is already in the array, or you can use a Set object.

